               <persName xml:lang="gez" corresp="#n2" type="normalized">Haliba Wangel</persName>
               
               <persName><roleName type="title">azzāž </roleName></persName>
                  <occupation type="military">leader</occupation>
                  
               <floruit notBefore="1574" notAfter="1596">He was a trusted <roleName type="title">azzāž </roleName>at the court of <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS8550sardaDe"/>. As such he was appointed commander of a newly organized guard regiment qʷǝrbān in <date>1574</date>
                  and served loyally his sovereign both as war lord and diplomat.  A year later, in <date>1575</date>, he was sent as a head of delegation of high ecclesiastics to bahǝr nagāš 
                  <persName ref="PRS10343Yeshaq"/> to pledge loyality to the emperor. He is also known to have taken part with his regiment in a successful campaign of the Emperor against the 
                  <persName ref="ETH1274Betaes"/>prince <persName ref="PRS5842Kalef"/> in October <date>1597</date>.
               </floruit>   
                 
